Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?Stage=20B:=20marryModule()=20engine=20=E2=80=94?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20one=20verified=20path=20for=20marrying=20modules?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Collapses the 10 scattered derive->write->verify sync/marry paths into one
pure-logic engine. Given an authoritative source (BCM/RFHUB/95640) and an
unmarried target (GPEC2A PCM, RFHUB Gen1/Gen2/XC2268, BCM, 95640), it resolves
the RFH-form SEC16 root, derives the target secret via immoSecret + the
canonical securityBytes writers, then RE-PARSES the output and asserts the
secret reads back exactly as derived — refusing (ok:false, no file) on any
mismatch.

Ultimate-machine gates: blank/virgin source refused; writing an UNVERIFIED
target writer (RFHUB Gen1 / XC2268, per algoProvenance) requires explicit
allowUnverifiedTarget; every result carries the writer's grounding for the UI.
Folds in the 95640 SEC16-mirror writer that previously lived inline in
ModuleSync. 14-case node harness + vitest suite; all green.
